


IPv4 : 32 bit = 2^32 = 4,294,967,296 IPv4 addresses
Ipv6 : 128 bit = 2^128 = 


IPv4 has 5 Classes, Only 3 classes allocated for general public usage

Class A : 0 - 126
Class B : 128 - 191
Class C : 192 - 223

Class D : broadcosting/multicasting purpose
Class E : R&D purpose

127 -> loopback/localhost IP address


Using this : 192.168.0.0 - 192.168.255.255 : Private IPs and Its free to use.

Class A : 0 - 126   : 10.0.0.0 - 10.255.255.255 
Class B : 128 - 191 : 172.16.0.0 - 172.31.255.255
Class C : 192 - 223 : 192.168.0.0 - 192.168.255.255



