============================================

general network 2 IPs reserved (Network ID and Brodcost ID)
AWS Reserves 3 on top of general networks (2 DNS servers and 1 Future usage)


192.168.100.10/32

/32 = 32 - 32 = 0 = 2^0 = 1 IP
/31 = 32 - 31 = 1 = 2^1 = 2 IPs
/30 = 32 - 30 = 2 = 2^2 = 4 IPs
/29 = 32 - 29 = 3 = 2^3 = 8 IPs

/28 = 32 - 28 = 4 = 2^4 = 16 IPs - 5 = 11 Usable IPs
/24 = 32 - 24 = 8 = 2^8 = 256 IPs - 5 = 251 Usable IPs
/20 = 4096
/16 = 32 - 16 = 16 = 2^16 = 65536 - 5 = 65531 Usable IPs

Min VPC Supports : /28 
Max VPC supports : /24 


/24 = 256 IPs = 5 IPs reserved(customer cannot use) : 251 Usable IPs













